1. Install bootstrap source as node package. Install sass as command line tool:

npm init
npm install bootstrap --save
sudo apt-get install ruby-full
sudo gem install sass

2. To run Sass from the command line, just use:

sass input.scss output.css

3. You can also tell Sass to watch the file and update the CSS every time the Sass file changes:

project/
    node_modules/
        bootstrap/
    scss/
        main.scss
    css/
        main.css
    index.html

$ cd project/
$ sass --watch scss/main.scss:css/main.css

4. Install SCSS package in Sublime 3 (CSS and SCSS highlighter)

ctrl+shift+p
Package Control: Install Package
search for 'SCSS'
click 'SCSS' 
ctrl+shift+p
search for 'SCSS'
click 'Syntax: SCSS'

5. You will find the complete list of Bootstrapâ€™s variables in scss/_variables.scss.
